# Writing Trigger.dev tasks - Continue.dev
created: 2025-08-21, last updated: 2026-03-29, [Read more](https://www.continue.dev/trigger-dev/writing-tasks)

Trigger.dev v3 tasks must be created using task() from @trigger.dev/sdk/v3 with exported functions and unique IDs, avoiding the deprecated client.defineJob() pattern that will break applications.
Tasks support configuration options like retry policies, queues, machine specs, lifecycle hooks, scheduling, schema validation, and can be triggered from backends or other tasks using methods like trigger(), triggerAndWait(), and batch operations
…
```
export const parentTask = task({
id: "parent-task",
run: async (payload: string) => {
const result = await childTask.triggerAndWait("some-data");
console.log("Result", result);
//...do stuff with the result
},
});
```
…
### batch.triggerAndWait()
Batch triggers multiple different tasks and waits for all results.
…
```
await childTask.trigger(
{ foo: "bar" },
{ idempotencyKey, idempotencyKeyTTL: "60s" }
);
await wait.for({ seconds: 61 });
// Key expired, will trigger a new run
await childTask.trigger({ foo: "bar" }, { idempotencyKey });
```

